      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE SASSY BOY (3) worked to find the lead and kept kicking to return to winning ways last time out over 1720m at Young, getting home 2.5 metres ahead of his rivals. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and is good enough to put himself in the winners' stall. CONSORT NZ (5) last appeared when a seventh over 1710m at Goulburn on November 25, capping off a fine prep that saw him salute on two occasions. Likely to run a big race to kick off this campaign. MIKI SING (6) failed last start over 2150m at Carrick five months ago. Well-placed here and a forward showing is anticipated. SET PLAY (7) could only finish seventh over 2270m at this circuit most recently. Open to improvement and is in the mix for some minor money.",
